folks whose pet is actually the better tank. I surpassed my pet's ability to tank a long time ago and the groups I play with can earn 3 AA's an hour these days. Again, its about efficiency of the tactic. If you are using the tactic of sitting your pet down so it can regen while its being beat senseless I guarantee you are not earning xp very efficiently or effectively. Group's and duo's are the best way to get xp and imo have fun. Mages are a super partner, their abilities complement ours extremely well.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;br&gt;The thing some people seem to be missing: With Pet Hold, you can force your pet to not attack, even when it's being hit, so it can regen at sitting speeds while under attack. With a couple HP buffs, or some extra spell regen, this can be more than enough to hold up under a lot of attacks. (Admittedly, it probably couldn't handle 900+ hits or anything insane like that, but if you need to park some trash mob out of the way for a while, this is a great trick.)</description>
